Convert the main component as a bipartitle graph into two unipartite (or one-mode) graphs by referring to the following code block.

Shyni David, Alex Duquenne, Matthew Fleming and Shannon Poffenberger has zero betweenness centrality in the persons graph.

What does it mean to have a zero betweeness centrality in this context?

Betweenness centrality gives high score to nodes sitting in critical junctions for example node between two highly connected group of nodes. So in persons network, the nodes with zero betweenness are the nodes with single edge, that is a node that is connected to the rest of the network with only one edge.
